          "treatment": "ABCDE approach. IV access 2 large-bore. Fluid bolus 500mL crystalloid (caution if cardiogenic). Identify type: cold clammy+JVP flat=hypovolemic, cold clammy+JVP up=cardiogenic, warm+JVP flat=distributive, JVP up+muffled=obstructive. Vasopressors if MAP <65 after fluids. Norepinephrine first-line. Treat underlying cause."
